obj_root_law_sections_36:
  sectionId (3921)
  sectionNo (36)
  orderNo 37
  title `Central Government to develop national strategies and plans for conservation, promotion and sustainable use of biological diversity.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_000010_200318_1517807327125&sectionId=3921&sectionno=36&orderno=37&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_000010_200318_1517807327125
obj_root_law_sections_36_content:
  string
  line `^1[Central Government to develop national strategies and plans for conservation, promotion and sustainable use of biological diversity.]--(1) The Central Government shall ^2[in consultation with the State Government and Union territories] develop national strategies, plans, programmes for the`
  line `conservation and promotion and sustainable use of biological diversity including measures for identification and monitoring of areas rich in biological resources, promotion of in situ, and ex situ, ^3[conservation of biological resources, including cultivars, folk varieties and landraces, incentives] for research, training and public education to increase awareness with respect to biodiversity.`
  line
  line `(2) Where the Central Government has reason to believe that any area rich in biological diversity, biological resources and their habitats is being threatened by overuse, abuse or neglect, it shall issue directives to the concerned State Government to take immediate ameliorative measures, offering such State Government any technical and other assistance that is possible to be provided or needed.`
  line
  line `(3) The Central Government shall, as far as practicable wherever it deems appropriate, integrate the conservation, promotion and sustainable use of biological diversity into relevant ^4[sectoral policies or cross-sectoral plans and programmes].`
  line
  line `(4) The Central Government shall undertake measure,--`
  line
  line `(i) wherever necessary, for assessment of environmental impact of that project which is likely to have adverse effect on biological diversity, with a view to avoid or minimise such effects and where appropriate provide for public participation in such assessment;`
  line
  line `(ii) to regulate, manage or control the risks associated with the use and release of living modified organisms resulting from biotechnology likely to have adverse impact on the conservation and sustainable use of biological diversity and human health.`
  line
  line `(5) The Central Government shall endeavour to respect and protect the knowledge of local people relating to biological diversity, as recommended by the National Biodiversity Authority through such measures, which may include registration of such knowledge at the local, State or national levels, and other measures for protection, including sui generis system.`
  line
  line `^5[(6) The Central Government shall involve the National Biodiversity Authority or State Biodiversity Boards to undertake measures for conservation and sustainable use of biological diversity or traditional knowledge associated thereto.]`
  line
  line `Explanation. -- For the purposes of this section,--`
  line
  line `(a) "ex situ conservation" means the conservation of components of biological diversity outside`
  line `their natural habitats;`
  line
  line `(b) "in situ conservation" means the conservation of ecosystems and natural habitats and the maintenance and recovery of viable populations of species in their natural surroundings and, in the case of domesticated or cultivated species, in the surroundings where they have developed their distinctive properties.`
obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 10 of 2023, s. 25, for the marginal heading (w.e.f. 1-4-2024).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by s. 25, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-4-2024).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 25, ibid., for "conservation of biological resources, incentives" (w.e.f. 1-4-2024).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by s. 25, ibid., for "sectoral or cross-sectoral plans, programmes and policies" (w.e.f. 1-4-2024).`
  line
  line `5. Ins. by s. 25, ibid (w.e.f. 1-4-2024).`
  line
  line `6. Ins. by s. 26, ibid (w.e.f. 1-4-2024).`
obj_root_law_sections_36_a:
  sectionId (83509)
  sectionNo 36A
  orderNo 38
  title `Measures to be taken by National Biodiversity Authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 26, Act 10 of 2023 (w.e.f. 1-4-2024).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_000010_200318_1517807327125&sectionId=83509&sectionno=36A&orderno=38&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_000010_200318_1517807327125
obj_root_law_sections_36_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[36A. Measures to be taken by National Biodiversity Authority.--The Central Government may authorise National Biodiversity Authority or any other organisation to take any measure necessary to monitor and regulate within the territory of India, the access and utilisation of biological resources obtained from a foreign country in order to meet the international obligations to which India is a`
  line signatory.
obj_root_law_sections_36_b:
  sectionId (83510)
  sectionNo 36B
  orderNo 39
  title `State Government to develop strategies and plans for conservation and sustainable use of biological diversity.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_b_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 10 of 2023, s. 26, (w.e.f. 1-4-2024).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_000010_200318_1517807327125&sectionId=83510&sectionno=36B&orderno=39&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_000010_200318_1517807327125
obj_root_law_sections_36_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[36B. State Government to develop strategies and plans for conservation and sustainable use of biological diversity.--(1) The State Government shall develop strategies, plans, programmes for the conservation and promotion and sustainable use of biological diversity, including measures for indentification and monitoring of areas rich in biological resources, promotion of in situ, and ex situ, conservation of biological resources, including cultivars, folk varieties and landraces, incentives for research, training and public education to increase awareness with respect to biodiversity, in conformity`
  line `with the national strategies, plans and programmes.`
  line
  line `(2) The State Government shall, as far as practicable, wherever it deems appropriate, integrate the conservation, promotion and sustainable use of biological diversity into relevant sectoral policies or cross-sectoral plans and programmes.]`
obj_root_law_sections_37:
  sectionId (3922)
  sectionNo (37)
  orderNo 40
  title `Biodiversity heritage sites.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_37_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_000010_200318_1517807327125&sectionId=3922&sectionno=37&orderno=40&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_000010_200318_1517807327125
obj_root_law_sections_37_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1) Without prejudice to any other law for the time being in force,`
  line `based on the recommendations of the State Biodiversity Board, the State Government may, from time to time, notify in the Official Gazette, areas of biodiversity importance as biodiversity heritage sites under this Act:`
  line
  line `Provided that the State Biodiversity Board shall consult the local body and the Biodiversity`
  line `Management Committee concerned before making such recommendations.]`
  line
  line `(2) The State Government, in consultation with the Central Government, may frame rules for the management and conservation of all the ^2[biodiversity heritage sites].`
  line
  line `(3) The State Government shall frame schemes for compensating or rehabilitating any person or section of people economically affected by such notification.`
obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 10 of 2023, s. 27, for sub-section (1) (w.e.f. 1-4-2024).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 27, ibid., for "heritage sites" (w.e.f. 1-4-2024)`
obj_root_law_sections_38:
  sectionId (3923)
  sectionNo (38)
  orderNo 41
  title `Power of Central Government to notify threatened species.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_38_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 10 of 2023, s. 28 (w.e.f. 1-4-2024).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_000010_200318_1517807327125&sectionId=3923&sectionno=38&orderno=41&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_000010_200318_1517807327125
obj_root_law_sections_38_content:
  string
  line `Without prejudice to the`
  line `provisions of any other law for the time being in force, the Central Government, in consultation with the`
  line `concerned State Government, may from time to time notify any species which is on the verge of`
  line `extinction or likely to become extinct in the near future as a threatened species and prohibit or regulate`
  line `collection thereof for any purpose and take appropriate steps to rehabilitate and preserve those species.`
  line
  line `^1[Provided that the Central Government may delegate such power to the State Government:`
  line
  line `Provided further that where such power is delegated to the State Government, it shall consult the`
  line `National Biodiversity Authority before issuing any such notification.]`
obj_root_law_sections_39:
  sectionId (3924)
  sectionNo (39)
  orderNo 42
  title `Power of Central Government to designate repositories.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_39_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_000010_200318_1517807327125&sectionId=3924&sectionno=39&orderno=42&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_000010_200318_1517807327125
obj_root_law_sections_39_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may,`
  line `in consultation with the National Biodiversity Authority, designate institutions as repositories under this`
  line `Act for different categories of biological resources.`
  line
  line `(2) The repositories shall keep in safe custody the biological material including voucher specimens`
  line `deposited with them.`
  line
  line `(3) Any new tax on discovered by any person shall be notified to the repositories or any institution`
  line `designated for this purpose and he shall deposit the voucher specimens with such repository or institution.`
obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_40:
  sectionId (3925)
  sectionNo (40)
  orderNo 43
  title `Provisions of this Act not to apply in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_40_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 10 of 2023, s. 29, for section 40 (w.e.f. 1-4-2024).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_000010_200318_1517807327125&sectionId=3925&sectionno=40&orderno=43&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_000010_200318_1517807327125
obj_root_law_sections_40_content:
  string
  line `^1[40. Provisions of this Act not to apply in certain cases. --Notwithstanding anything contained in this Act, the Central Government may, in consultation with the National Biodiversity Authority, by notification in the Official Gazette, declare that all or any of the provisions of this Act shall not apply to biological resources when normally traded as commodities or to the items derived from them, including agricultural wastes, as notified and cultivated medicinal plants and their products for entities covered`
  line `under section 7, registered as per the regulations made or as may prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided that no exemption shall be made for the activities referred to in sub-sections (1) and (2) of section 6.]`
obj_root_law_sections_41:
  sectionId (3926)
  sectionNo (41)
  orderNo 44
  title `Constitutions of Biodiversity Management Committees.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_41_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_000010_200318_1517807327125&sectionId=3926&sectionno=41&orderno=44&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_000010_200318_1517807327125
obj_root_law_sections_41_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1) Every local body at the Gram Panchayat level in the rural areas and at the Nagar Panchayat or Municipal Committee at Municipal Corporation level in the urban areas shall constitute a Biodiversity Management Committee (by whatever name called) within its area for the purpose of promoting conservation, sustainable use and documentation of biological diversity including preservation of habitats, conservation of landraces, folk varieties, farmers' varieties, and cultivars, domesticated stocks and breeds of animals, living things in water bodies and microorganisms and chronicling of knowledge relating to biological diversity:`
  line
  line `Provided that the State Government may constitute Biodiversity Management Committees at the intermediate or district Panchayat level for achieving the objectives of the Act.`
  line
  line `(1A) The functions of Biodiversity Management Committee so constituted shall include conservation, sustainable use and documentation of biological diversity, including conservation of habitats, landraces, folk varieties, cultivars, domesticated breeds of animals, and microorganisms, and chronicling of traditional knowledge associated thereto relating to biological diversity:`
  line
  line `(1B) The composition of the Biodiversity Management Committee shall be such as may be prescribed by the State Government:`
  line
  line `Provided that the number of members of the said Committee shall not be less than seven and not exceeding eleven.]`
  line
  line `(2) The National Biodiversity Authority and the State Biodiversity Boards shall consult the Biodiversity Management Committees while taking any decision relating to the use of biological resources ^2[or traditional knowledge associated thereto] occurring within the territorial jurisdiction of the Biodiversity Management Committee.`
  line
  line `^3[Explanation. --For the purposes of this section--`
  line
  line `(a) "cultivar" means a veriety of plant that has originated and persisted under cultivation or was specifically bred for the purpose of cultivation;`
  line
  line `(b) "folk variety" means a cultivated variety of plant that was developed, grown and exchanged informally among farmers;`
  line
  line `(c) "landrace" means primitive cultivar that was grown by ancient farmers and their successors;`
  line
  line `(d) "farmers' variety" means a veriety which--`
  line
  line `(i) has been traditionally cultivated and evolved by the farmers in their field; or`
  line
  line `(ii) is a wild relative or landrace of a veriety about which the farmers possess the common knowledge.]`
  line
  line `(3) The Biodiversity Management Committees may levy charges by way of collection fees from any person for accessing or collecting any biological resource for commercial purposes from areas falling within its territorial jurisdiction.`
obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 10 of 2023, s. 30, for sub-section (1) (w.e.f. 1-4-2024).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 30, ibid., for "and knowledge associated with such resources" (w.e.f. 1-4-2024).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by s. 30, ibid., (w.e.f. 1-4-2024).`
obj_root_law_sections_42:
  sectionId (3927)
  sectionNo (42)
  orderNo 45
  title `Grants to Local Biodiversity Fund.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_42_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_000010_200318_1517807327125&sectionId=3927&sectionno=42&orderno=45&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_000010_200318_1517807327125
obj_root_law_sections_42_content:
  string
  line `The State Government may, after due appropriation made`
  line `by State Legislature by law in this behalf, pay to the Local Biodiversity Funds by way of grants or loans`
  line `such sums of money as the State Government may think fit for being utilised for the purposes of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_43:
  sectionId (3928)
  sectionNo (43)
  orderNo 46
  title `Constitution of Local Biodiversity Fund.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_43_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 10 of 2023, s. 31, for clause (e) (w.e.f. 1-4-2024).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_000010_200318_1517807327125&sectionId=3928&sectionno=43&orderno=46&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_000010_200318_1517807327125
obj_root_law_sections_43_content:
  string
  line `(1) There shall be constituted a Fund to be called the`
  line `Local Biodiversity Fund at every area notified by the State Government where any institution of`
  line `self-government is functioning and there shall be credited thereto--`
  line
  line `(a) any grants and loans made under section 42;`
  line
  line `(b) any grants or loans made by the National Biodiversity Authority;`
  line
  line `(c) any grants or loans made by the State Biodiversity Boards;`
  line
  line `(d) fees referred to in sub-section (3) of section 41 received by the Biodiversity Management`
  line Committees;
  line
  line `^1[(e) benefit sharing amount and all other sums received by the Local Biodiversity Fund from such other sources as may be decided by the State Government.]`
obj_root_law_sections_44:
  sectionId (3929)
  sectionNo (44)
  orderNo 47
  title `Application of Local Biodiversity Fund.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_44_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 10 of 2023, s. 32, for section 44 (w.e.f. 1-4-2024).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_000010_200318_1517807327125&sectionId=3929&sectionno=44&orderno=47&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_000010_200318_1517807327125
obj_root_law_sections_44_content:
  string
  line `^1[44. Application of Local Biodiversity Fund.--(1) The Local Biodiversity Fund shall be utilised in accordance with the regulations and the guidelines made in this behalf, for--`
  line
  line `(a) the conservation and promotion of biodiversity including restoration of areas falling within the jurisdiction of concerned local body;`
  line
  line `(b) the socio-economic development of the community without compromising the conservation concerns; and`
  line
  line `(c) the administrative expenses of the Biodiversity Management Committee.`
  line
  line `(2) The Fund shall be utilised in such manner as may be prescribed by the State Government.].`
obj_root_law_sections_45:
  sectionId (3930)
  sectionNo (45)
  orderNo 48
  title `Annual statement of Biodiversity Management Committees.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_45_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 10 of 2023, s. 33, for section 45 (w.e.f. 1-4-2024).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_000010_200318_1517807327125&sectionId=3930&sectionno=45&orderno=48&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_000010_200318_1517807327125
obj_root_law_sections_45_content:
  string
  line `^1[45. Annual statement of Biodiversity Management Committees.--The custodian of the Local Biodiversity Fund shall prepare, in such form and during each financial year at such time as may be prescribed by the State Government, its annual statement giving a full account of its activities during the previous financial year, and submit the same to the local body concerned with a copy to the State`
  line `Biodiversity Board.]`
obj_root_law_sections_46:
  sectionId (3931)
  sectionNo (46)
  orderNo 49
  title `Audit of accounts of Biodiversity Management Committees.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_46_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 10 of 2023, s. 34, for section 46 (w.e.f. 1-4-2024).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_000010_200318_1517807327125&sectionId=3931&sectionno=46&orderno=49&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_000010_200318_1517807327125
obj_root_law_sections_46_content:
  string
  line `^1[46. Audit of accounts of Biodiversity Management Committees.-- (1) The Biodiversity Management Committee shall maintain the accounts which shall be audited in such manner as may be prescribed by the State Government.`
  line
  line `(2) The Biodiversity Management Committee shall furnish to the local body concerned and to the State Biodiversity Board, before such date as may be prescribed by the State Government, its audited copy of accounts together with auditor's report thereon.]`
obj_root_law_sections_47:
  sectionId (3932)
  sectionNo (47)
  orderNo 50
  title `Annual report, etc., of Biodiversity Management Committee to be submitted to District Magistrate.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_47_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_000010_200318_1517807327125&sectionId=3932&sectionno=47&orderno=50&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_000010_200318_1517807327125
obj_root_law_sections_47_content:
  string
  line `Every local body constituting a Biodiversity Management Committee under sub-section (1) of section 41, shall cause, the annual report and audited copy of accounts together with auditor's report`
  line `thereon referred to in sections 45 and 46, respectively and relating to such Committee to be submitted to`
  line `the District Magistrate having jurisdiction over the area of the local body.`
obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_48:
  sectionId (3933)
  sectionNo (48)
  orderNo 51
  title `National Biodiversity Authority to be bound by the directions given by Central Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_48_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_48_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_000010_200318_1517807327125&sectionId=3933&sectionno=48&orderno=51&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_000010_200318_1517807327125
obj_root_law_sections_48_content:
  string
  line `(1) Without prejudice to the foregoing provisions of this Act, the National Biodiversity`
  line `Authority shall, in the discharge of its functions and duties under this Act, be bound by such directions on`
  line `questions of policy as the Central Government may give in writing to it from time to time:`
  line
  line `Provided that the National Biodiversity Authority shall, as far as practicable, be given opportunity to`
  line `express its views before any direction is given under this sub-section.`
  line
  line `(2) The decision of the Central Government whether a question is one of policy or not shall be final.`
obj_root_law_sections_48_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_49:
  sectionId (3934)
  sectionNo (49)
  orderNo 52
  title `Power of State Government to give directions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_49_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_000010_200318_1517807327125&sectionId=3934&sectionno=49&orderno=52&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_000010_200318_1517807327125
obj_root_law_sections_49_content:
  string
  line `(1) Without prejudice to the foregoing`
  line `provisions of this Act, the State Biodiversity Board shall, in the discharge of its functions and duties`
  line `under this Act, be bound by such directions on questions of policy as the State Government may give in`
  line `writing to it from time to time:`
  line
  line `Provided that the State Biodiversity Board shall, as far as practicable, be given an opportunity to`
  line `express its views before any direction is given under this sub-section.`
  line
  line `(2) The decision of the State Government whether a question is one of policy or not shall be final.`
obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_50:
  sectionId (3935)
  sectionNo (50)
  orderNo 53
  title `Settlement of disputes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_50_content
  footnotes `1. The words "between State Biodiversity Boards" omitted by Act 10 of 2023, s. 35, (w.e.f. 1-4-2024).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_000010_200318_1517807327125&sectionId=3935&sectionno=50&orderno=53&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_000010_200318_1517807327125
obj_root_law_sections_50_content:
  string
  line `50. Settlement of disputes ^1***.--(1) If a dispute arises between the`
  line `National Biodiversity Authority and a State Biodiversity Board, the said Authority or the Board, as the`
  line `case may be, may prefer an appeal to the Central Government within such time as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) Every appeal made under sub-section (1) shall be in such form as may be prescribed by the`
  line `Central Government.`
  line
  line `(3) The procedure for disposing of an appeal shall be such as may be prescribed by the Central`
  line `Government:`
  line
  line `Provided that before disposing of an appeal, the parties shall be given a reasonable opportunity of`
  line `being heard.`
  line
  line `(4) If a dispute arises between the State Biodiversity Boards, the Central Government shall refer the`
  line `same to the National Biodiversity Authority.`
  line
  line `(5) While adjudicating any dispute under sub-section (4), the National Biodiversity Authority shall be`
  line `guided by the principles of natural justice and shall follow such procedure as may be prescribed by the`
  line `Central Government.`
  line
  line `(6) The National Biodiversity Authority shall have, for the purposes of discharging its functions under`
  line `this section, the same powers as are vested in a civil court under the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908`
  line `(5 of 1908) in respect of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) summoning and enforcing the attendance of any person and examining him on oath;`
  line
  line `(b) requiring the discovery and production of documents;`
  line
  line `(c) receiving evidence on affidavits;`
  line
  line `(d) issuing commissions for the examination of witnesses or documents;`
  line
  line `(e) reviewing its decisions;`
  line
  line `(f) dismissing an application for default or deciding it ex parte;`
  line
  line `(g) setting aside any order of dismissal of any application for default or any order passed by it ex parte;`
  line
  line `(h) any other matter which may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(7) Every proceeding before the National Biodiversity Authority shall be deemed to be a judicial`
  line `proceeding within the meaning of sections 193 and 228, and for the purpose of section 196, of the Indian`
  line `Penal Code (45 of 1860) and the National Biodiversity Authority shall be deemed to be a civil court for`
  line `all the purposes of section 195 and Chapter XXV1 of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974).`
obj_root_law_sections_51:
  sectionId (3936)
  sectionNo (51)
  orderNo 54
  title `Members, officers, etc., of National Biodiversity Authority and State Biodiversity Board deemed to be public servants.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_51_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_51_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_000010_200318_1517807327125&sectionId=3936&sectionno=51&orderno=54&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_000010_200318_1517807327125
obj_root_law_sections_51_content:
  string
  line `All members, officers and other employees of the National Biodiversity`
  line `Authority or the State Biodiversity Board shall be deemed, when acting or purporting to act in pursuance`
  line `of any of the provisions of this Act, to be public servants within the meaning of section 21 of the Indian`
  line `Penal Code (45 of 1860).`
obj_root_law_sections_51_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_52:
  sectionId (3937)
  sectionNo (52)
  orderNo 55
  title Appeal.
  content obj_root_law_sections_52_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_52_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_000010_200318_1517807327125&sectionId=3937&sectionno=52&orderno=55&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_000010_200318_1517807327125
obj_root_law_sections_52_content:
  string
  line `Any person, aggrieved by any determination of ^1[fair and equitable sharing of benefits or order or direction] of the National Biodiversity Authority or a State Biodiversity Board under this Act, may file an appeal to the High Court within thirty days from the date of communication to him, of the determination or order of the National Biodiversity Authority or the State Biodiversity Board, as the case may be:`
  line
  line `Provided that the High Court may, if it is satisfied that the appellant was prevented by sufficient cause from filing the appeal within the said period, allow it to be filed within a further period not exceeding sixty days.`
  line
  line `^2[Provided further that nothing contained in this section shall apply on and from the commencement of the National Green Tribunal Act, 2010 (19 of 2010):`
  line
  line `Provided also that any appeal pending before the High Court, before the commencement of the National Green Tribunal Act, 2010 (19 of 2010), shall continue to be heard and disposed of by the High Court as if the National Green Tribunal had not been established under section 3 of the National Green Tribunal Act, 2010.]`
obj_root_law_sections_52_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 10 of 2023, s. 36, for "benefit sharing or order" (w.e.f. 1-4-2024).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 19 of 2010, s. 36 and Schedule III (w. e. f. 18-10-2010).`
obj_root_law_sections_52_a:
  sectionId (3938)
  sectionNo 52A
  orderNo 56
  title `Appeal to National Green Tribunal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_52_a_content
  footnotes `1 Ins. by Act of 19 of 2010, s. 36 and Schedule III (w. e. f. 18-10-2010).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_000010_200318_1517807327125&sectionId=3938&sectionno=52A&orderno=56&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_000010_200318_1517807327125
obj_root_law_sections_52_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[ 52A. Appeal to National Green Tribunal.--Any person aggrieved by any determination of`
  line `benefit sharing or order of the National Biodiversity Authority or a State Biodiversity Board under this`
  line `Act, on or after the commencement of the National Green Tribunal Act, 2010 (19 of 2010), may file an`
  line `appeal to the National Green Tribunal establishment under section 3 of the National Green Tribunal Act,`
  line `2010, in accordance with the provisions of that Act.]`
obj_root_law_sections_53:
  sectionId (3939)
  sectionNo (53)
  orderNo 57
  title `Execution of determination or order.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_53_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_53_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_000010_200318_1517807327125&sectionId=3939&sectionno=53&orderno=57&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_000010_200318_1517807327125
obj_root_law_sections_53_content:
  string
  line `Every determination of ^1[fair and equitable sharing of`
  line `benefits] or order made by the National Biodiversity Authority or a State Biodiversity Board under this Act or the order made by the High Court ^2[or the National Green Tribunal] in any appeal against any determination or order of the National Biodiversity Authority or a State Biodiversity Board shall, on a certificate issued by any officer of the National Biodiversity Authority or a State Biodiversity Board or`
  line `the Registrar of the High Court ^2[or the Registrar of the National Green Tribunal], as the case may be, be`
  line `deemed to be decree of the civil court and shall be executable in the same manner as a decree of that`
  line court.
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section and section 52, the expression "State Biodiversity Board" includes the person or group of persons ^2[or body] to whom the powers or functions under sub-section (2) of section 22 have been delegated under the proviso to that sub-section and the certificate relating to such person or group of persons ^2[or body] under this section shall be issued by such person or group of persons ^2[or body], as the case may be.`
obj_root_law_sections_53_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 10 of 2023, s. 37, for "benefit sharing" (w.e.f. 1-4-2024).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by s. 37, ibid., (w.e.f. 1-4-2024)`
obj_root_law_sections_54:
  sectionId (3940)
  sectionNo (54)
  orderNo 58
  title `Protection of action taken in good faith.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_54_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_54_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_000010_200318_1517807327125&sectionId=3940&sectionno=54&orderno=58&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_000010_200318_1517807327125
obj_root_law_sections_54_content:
  string
  line `No suit, prosecution or other legal proceedings shall`
  line `lie against the Central Government or the State Government or any officer of the Central Government or`
  line `State Government or any member, officer or employee of the National Biodiversity Authority or the State Biodiversity Board for anything which is in good faith done or intended to be done under this Act or`
  line `the rules or regulations made thereunder.`
obj_root_law_sections_54_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_55:
  sectionId (3941)
  sectionNo (55)
  orderNo 59
  title Penalties.
  content obj_root_law_sections_55_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 10 of 2023, s. 38, for section 55 (w.e.f. 1-4-2024).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_000010_200318_1517807327125&sectionId=3941&sectionno=55&orderno=59&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_000010_200318_1517807327125
obj_root_law_sections_55_content:
  string
  line `^1[55. Penalties.-- If any person or entity covered under sub-section (2) of section 3 or section 7 contravenes or attempts to contravene or abets the contravention of the provisions of section 3 or section 4 or section 6 or section 7, such person shall be liable to pay penalty which shall not be less than one lakh rupees, but which may extend to fifty lakh rupees, but where the damage caused exceeds the amount of`
  line `penalty, such penalty shall be commensurate with the damage caused, and in case, the failure or contravention continues, an additional penalty may be imposed, which shall not exceed one crore rupees and such penalty shall be decided by the adjudicating officer appointed under section 55A.]`
obj_root_law_sections_55_a:
  sectionId (83511)
  sectionNo 55A
  orderNo 60
  title `Adjudication of penalties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_55_a_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 10 of 2023, s. 38, or section 55 (w.e.f. 1-4-2024).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_000010_200318_1517807327125&sectionId=83511&sectionno=55A&orderno=60&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_000010_200318_1517807327125
obj_root_law_sections_55_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[55A. Adjudication of penalties.--(1) For the purposes of determining the penalties under section`
  line `55, the Central Government may appoint an officer not below the rank of Joint Secretary to the`
  line `Government of India or a Secretary to the State Government to be the adjudicating officer, to hold inquiry`
  line `in the prescribed manner and to impose the penalty so determined:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Central Government may appoint as many adjudicating officers as may be required.`
  line
  line `(2) While holding an inquiry, the adjudicating officer shall have power to summon and enforce the`
  line `attendance of any person acquainted with the facts and circumstances of the case to give evidence or to`
  line `produce any document, which in the opinion of the adjudicating officer, may be useful for, or relevant to,`
  line `the subject-matter of the inquiry and if, on such inquiry, he is satisfied that the person concerned has`
  line `failed to comply with the provisions of section 3 or section 4 or section 6 or section 7, he may impose`
  line `such penalty as he thinks fit in accordance with the provisions of section 55:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such penalty shall be imposed without giving the person concerned an opportunity of`
  line `being heard in the matter.`
  line
  line `(3) Any person aggrieved by the order made by the adjudicating officer under sub-section (2) may`
  line `prefer an appeal to the National Green Tribunal established under section 3 of the National Green`
  line `Tribunal Act, 2010 (19 of 2010).`
  line
  line `(4) Every appeal under sub-section (3) shall be filed within sixty days from the date on which the`
  line `copy of the order made by the adjudicating officer is received by the aggrieved person.`
  line
  line `(5) The National Green Tribunal may, after giving the parties to the appeal an opportunity of being`
  line `heard, pass such order as it thinks fit, confirming, modifying or setting aside the order appealed against.`
obj_root_law_sections_55_b:
  sectionId (83512)
  sectionNo 55B
  orderNo 61
  title `Power to enter, inspect, survey, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_55_b_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 10 of 2023, s. 38, for section 55 (w.e.f. 1-4-2024).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_000010_200318_1517807327125&sectionId=83512&sectionno=55B&orderno=61&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_000010_200318_1517807327125
obj_root_law_sections_55_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[55B. Power to enter, inspect, survey, etc.--Any authority or officer empowered by the Central Government may, for the purposes of carrying out inspection, survey or any such activity, have all or any of the following powers, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the power to enter upon any land, vehicle, or premises and to inspect, investigate, survey and collect information and make a map of the same and seize the materials and records;`
  line
  line `(b) the powers of a civil court to compel the attendance of anyone, including witnesses and`
  line `production of documents and materials objects;`
  line
  line `(c) the power to issue a search-warrant;`
  line
  line `(d) the power to hold an inquiry and in the course of such inquiry, receive and record evidence;`
  line
  line `(e) such other power as may be prescribed.]`
obj_root_law_sections_56:
  sectionId (3942)
  sectionNo (56)
  orderNo 62
  title `Penalty for contravention for directions or orders of Central Government, State Government, National Biodiversity Authority and State Biodiversity Boards.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_56_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_56_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_000010_200318_1517807327125&sectionId=3942&sectionno=56&orderno=62&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_000010_200318_1517807327125
obj_root_law_sections_56_content:
  string
  line `If any person`
  line `contravenes any direction given or order made by the Central Government, the State Government, the`
  line `National Biodiversity Authority or the State Biodiversity Board for which no punishment has been`
  line `separately provided under this Act, he shall be punished with a fine which may extend to one lakh rupees`
  line `and in case of a second or subsequent offence, with fine which may extend to two lakh rupees and in the`
  line `case of continuous contravention with additional fine which may extend to two lakh rupees every day`
  line `during which the default continues.`
obj_root_law_sections_56_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_57:
  sectionId (3943)
  sectionNo (57)
  orderNo 63
  title `Offences by companies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_57_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_57_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_000010_200318_1517807327125&sectionId=3943&sectionno=57&orderno=63&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_000010_200318_1517807327125
obj_root_law_sections_57_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where an offence or contravention under this Act has been`
  line `committed by a company, every person who at the time the offence or contravention was committed was`
  line `in charge of, and was responsible to, the company for the conduct of the business of the company, as well`
  line `as the company, shall be deemed to be guilty of the offence or contravention and shall be liable to be`
  line `proceeded against and punished accordingly:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this sub-section shall render any such person liable to any`
  line `punishment provided in this Act, if he proves that the offence or contravention was committed without his`
  line `knowledge or that he had exercised all due diligence to prevent the commission of such offence or`
  line contravention.
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), where an offence or contravention under`
  line `this Act has been committed by a company and it is proved that the offence or contravention has been`
  line `committed with the consent or connivance of, or is attributable to, any neglect on the part of any director,`
  line `manager, secretary or other officer of the company, such director, manager, secretary or other officer shall`
  line `also be deemed to be guilty of the offence or contravention and shall be liable to be proceeded against and`
  line `punished accordingly.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section,--`
  line
  line `(a) "company" means any body corporate and includes a firm or other association of individuals;`
  line and
  line
  line `(b) "director", in relation to a firm, means a partner in the firm.`
obj_root_law_sections_57_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_58:
  sectionId (3944)
  sectionNo (58)
  orderNo 64
  title Omitted.
  content obj_root_law_sections_58_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_58_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_000010_200318_1517807327125&sectionId=3944&sectionno=58&orderno=64&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_000010_200318_1517807327125
obj_root_law_sections_58_content:
  string
  line `. [Offences to be cognizable and non-bailable.]--Omitted by the Biological Diversity`
  line `(Amendment) Act, 2023 (10 of 2023), s. 39 (w.e.f. 1-4-2024).`
obj_root_law_sections_58_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_59:
  sectionId (3945)
  sectionNo (59)
  orderNo 65
  title `Act to have effect in addition to other Acts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_59_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_59_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_000010_200318_1517807327125&sectionId=3945&sectionno=59&orderno=65&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_000010_200318_1517807327125
obj_root_law_sections_59_content:
  string
  line `The provisions of this Act shall be in addition to,`
  line `and not in derogation of, the provisions in any other law, for the time being in force, relating to forests or`
  line wildlife.
obj_root_law_sections_59_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_59_a:
  sectionId (83513)
  sectionNo 59A
  orderNo 66
  title `Act not to apply to certain persons.`
  content `^1[59A. Act not to apply to certain persons.--The provision of this Act shall not apply to any person who has been given any approval or granted any right under any law relating to protection of plant varieties enacted by Parliament to the extent that such approvals or rights given under that Act does not require similar approval under this Act.]`
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 10 of 2023, s. 40 (w.e.f. 1-4-2024).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_000010_200318_1517807327125&sectionId=83513&sectionno=59A&orderno=66&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_000010_200318_1517807327125
obj_root_law_sections_60:
  sectionId (3946)
  sectionNo (60)
  orderNo 67
  title `Power of Central Government to give directions to State Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_60_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_60_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_000010_200318_1517807327125&sectionId=3946&sectionno=60&orderno=67&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_000010_200318_1517807327125
obj_root_law_sections_60_content:
  string
  line `The Central`
  line `Government may give directions to any State Government as to the carrying into execution in the State of`
  line `any of the provisions of this Act or of any rule or regulation or order made thereunder.`
obj_root_law_sections_60_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_61:
  sectionId (3947)
  sectionNo (61)
  orderNo 68
  title `Cognizance of offences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_61_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_61_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_000010_200318_1517807327125&sectionId=3947&sectionno=61&orderno=68&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_000010_200318_1517807327125
obj_root_law_sections_61_content:
  string
  line `No Court shall take cognizance of any offence under this Act except`
  line `on a ^1[written complaint] made by--`
  line
  line `(a) the Central Government or any authority or officer authorised in this behalf by that`
  line `Government; or`
  line
  line `(b) ^2[any person or a benefit claimer] who has given notice of not less than thirty days in the prescribed manner, of such offence and of his intention to make a complaint, to the Central Government or the authority or officer authorised as aforesaid.`
obj_root_law_sections_61_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 10 of 2023, s. 41, for "complaint" (w.e.f. 1-4-2024).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 41, ibid., for "any benefit claimer" (w.e.f. 1-4-2024).`
obj_root_law_sections_62:
  sectionId (3948)
  sectionNo (62)
  orderNo 69
  title `Power of Central Government to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_62_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_62_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_000010_200318_1517807327125&sectionId=3948&sectionno=62&orderno=69&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_000010_200318_1517807327125
obj_root_law_sections_62_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by`
  line `notification in the Official Gazette, make rules for carrying out the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `^1[(a) the manner of obtaining the certificate of origin under sub-section (2) of section 7;`
  line
  line `(aa) the books on the basis of which the certificate of origin to be issued, the manner of`
  line `maintaining such books and the manner of issuing such certificate under sub-section (3) of section 7;`
  line
  line `(ab) the terms and conditions of service of the Chairperson, Member-Secretary and other`
  line `members under section 9;]`
  line
  line `(b) powers and duties of the Chairperson under section 10;`
  line
  line `^2[(ba) the other functions to be performed by the Member-Secretary;]`
  line
  line `(c) procedure under sub-section (1) of section 12 in regard to transaction of business at meetings;`
  line
  line `(d) form of application and payment of fees for undertaking certain activities under`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 19;`
  line
  line `(e) the form and manner of making an application under sub-section (2) of section 19;`
  line
  line `^2[(ea) form of application and payment of fees under sub-section (1) of section 20;]`
  line
  line `(f) form of application and the manner for transfer of biological resource or knowledge under`
  line `sub-section (2) of section 20;`
  line
  line `(g) form in which, and the time of each financial year at which, the annual report of the National`
  line `Biodiversity Authority shall be prepared and the date before which its audited copy of accounts`
  line `together with auditor's report thereon shall be furnished under section 28;`
  line
  line `(h) form in which the annual statement of account shall be prepared under sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 29;`
  line
  line `(i) the time within which and the form in which, an appeal may be preferred, the procedure for`
  line `disposing of an appeal and the procedure for adjudication, under section 50;`
  line
  line `(j) the additional matter in which the National Biodiversity Authority may exercise powers of the`
  line `civil court under clause (h) of sub-section (6) of section 50;`
  line
  line `^2[(ja) the manner of holding inquiry by the adjudicating officer under section 55A;`
  line
  line `(jb) the other power under clause (e) of section 55B;]`
  line
  line `(k) the manner of giving notice under clause (b) of section 61;`
  line
  line `(l) any other matter which is to be, or may be, prescribed, or in respect of which provision is to`
  line `be made, by rules.`
  line
  line `(3) Every rule made under this section and every regulation made under this Act shall be laid, as soon`
  line `as may be after it is made, before each House of Parliament, while it is in session or a total period of thirty`
  line `days which may be comprised in one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the`
  line `expiry of the session immediately following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses`
  line `agree in making any modification in the rule or regulation or both Houses agree that the rule or regulation`
  line `should not be made, the rule or regulation shall thereafter have effect only in such modified form or be of`
  line `no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that any such modification or annulment shall be without`
  line `prejudice to the validity of anything previously done under that rule or regulation.`
obj_root_law_sections_62_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 10 of 2023, s. 42, for clause (a) (w.e.f. 1-4-2024).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by s. 42, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-4-2024).`
obj_root_law_sections_63:
  sectionId (3949)
  sectionNo (63)
  orderNo 70
  title `Power of State Government to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_63_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_63_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_000010_200318_1517807327125&sectionId=3949&sectionno=63&orderno=70&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_000010_200318_1517807327125
obj_root_law_sections_63_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Government may, by notification in`
  line `the Official Gazette, make rules for carrying out the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the other functions to be performed by the State Biodiversity Board under clause (c) of section`
  line 23;
  line
  line `(b) the form in which the prior intimation shall be given under sub-section (1) of section 24;`
  line
  line `(c) the form in which, and the time of each financial year at which, the annual report shall be`
  line `prepared under section 33;`
  line
  line `(d) the manner of maintaining and auditing the accounts of the State Biodiversity Board and the`
  line `date before which its audited copy of the accounts together with auditor's report thereon shall be`
  line `furnished under section 34;`
  line
  line `(e) management and conservation of national heritage sites under section 37;`
  line
  line `(f) the manner of management and custody of the Local Biodiversity Fund and the purposes for`
  line `which such Fund shall be applied under sub-section (1) of section 44;`
  line
  line `(g) the form of annual report and the time at which such report shall be prepared during each`
  line `financial year under section 45;`
  line
  line `(h) the manner of maintaining and auditing the accounts of the Local Biodiversity Fund and the`
  line `date before which its audited copy of the accounts together with auditor's report thereon shall be`
  line `furnished under section 46;`
  line
  line `(i) any other matter which is to be, or may be, specified.`
  line
  line `(3) Every rule made by the State Government under this section shall be laid, as soon as may be after`
  line `it is made, before each House of the State Legislature where it consists of two Houses, or where such`
  line `Legislature consists of one House, before that House.`
obj_root_law_sections_63_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_64:
  sectionId (3950)
  sectionNo (64)
  orderNo 71
  title `Power to make regulations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_64_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_64_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_000010_200318_1517807327125&sectionId=3950&sectionno=64&orderno=71&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_000010_200318_1517807327125
obj_root_law_sections_64_content:
  string
  line `The National Biodiversity Authority shall, with the previous`
  line `approval of the Central Government, by notification in the Official Gazette, make regulations for carrying`
  line `out the purposes of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_64_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_65:
  sectionId (3951)
  sectionNo (65)
  orderNo 72
  title `Power to remove difficulties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_65_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_65_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_000010_200318_1517807327125&sectionId=3951&sectionno=65&orderno=72&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_000010_200318_1517807327125
obj_root_law_sections_65_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any difficulty arises in giving effect to the provisions of`
  line `this Act, the Central Government may, by order, not inconsistent with the provisions of this Act, remove`
  line `the difficulty:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such order shall be made after the expiry of a period of two years from the`
  line `commencement of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Every order made under this section shall be laid, as soon as may be, after it is made, before each`
  line `House of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_65_footnotes:
  string
  line
